{"embedder":"mock","model":"mock-lexical-256","dim":256,"chunks":[{"id":"pcos_overview-0","text":"What PCOS is\nPolycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is a common hormonal condition affecting women of reproductive age. It is a leading cause of irregular periods and difficulty getting pregnant, but it can be managed.\n\nCommon signs\nSigns may include irregular or missed periods, extra hair on the face or body, acne, weight gain, and trouble conceiving. Not every woman has every sign. PCOS is diagnosed by a doctor, often with an examination, blood tests, and sometimes an ultrasound — it cannot be confirmed from symptoms alone.","title":"Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)","source":"WHO fact sheet (sample seed — replace with the licensed source text before submission)","url":"https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/polycystic-ovary-syndrome","embedding":[0.04471018340098959,0.06706527510148438,0,0,0.11177545850247397,0.022355091700494795,0.022355091700494795,0.04471018340098959,0.022355091700494795,0.06706527510148438,0,0,0,0,0.08942036680197918,0.04471018340098959,0.15648564190346356,0.022355091700494795,0.04471018340098959,0,0.04471018340098959,0.17884073360395836,0,0.022355091700494795,0.13413055020296877,0,0,0.04471018340098959,0.06706527510148438,0.06706527510148438,0,0,0.11177545850247397,0.08942036680197918,0.20119582530445315,0.04471018340098959,0.06706527510148438,0,0.022355091700494795,0.04471018340098959,0.022355091700494795,0.022355091700494795,0.04471018340098959,0.022355091700494795,0.13413055020296877,0,0,0.04471018340098959,0,0.022355091700494795,0,0.022355091700494795,0,0,0.08942036680197918,0.022355091700494795,0.022355091700494795,0.04471018340098959,0,0,0,0.06706527510148438,0,0,0.022355091700494795,0.11177545850247397,0,0.04471018340098959,0.04471018340098959,0,0.06706527510148438,0.11177545850247397,0,0.04471018340098959,0.022355091700494795,0.06706527510148438,0.022355091700494795,0.04471018340098959,0.022355091700494795,0,0,0.11177545850247397